<h2>Jun Seba (also known as "Nujabes") was truly a one of a kind artist that could speak to your soul through the amount of musical talent this individual possessed.</p></h2>

    </div>
</div>

<div class="clearfix">
	<div class="row2">

<p><img src="nuja3.jpg" alt="Image" style="width: 25%">

<h2>A record label founder, record-store owner, and hip hop groundbreaker here in Tokyo, it’s hard to imagine what Japan’s hip hop scene would look like without his efforts. Though a little more elusive than many other past hip hop icons, there’s a bit to learn about this genre pushing producer.</p></h2>

<h1> Influences</h1>

<p><img src="nuja6.gif" alt="Image" style="width: 25%">
<h2>Nujabes also heavily influenced/inspired music artists like Jaden Smith, Fat Jon and animated TV shows by blending the elements jazz influences and laidback production to his craft of Hip-Hop beats. His music attributed most notably to the anime series, <i>Samurai Champloo.</i><p></h2>


